sxhwUpLink.name: sxhwUpLink
sxhwUpLink.description: Specifies whether the Up-Link I/O module is existed

sxhwUpLinkManufData.name: sxhwUpLinkManufData
sxhwUpLinkManufData.description: This is a 32-byte array which contains the part number, serial number, and hardware revision level of the Up-Link I/O module. This array is valid only when the sxhwUplink is true. If sxhwUplink is false, it returns an error

sxadminExtraTrunkGrouping.name: sxadminExtraTrunkGrouping
sxadminExtraTrunkGrouping.description: If true(1), then as many as 8 trunk groups may be created, rather than the default limit of 4 trunk groups. When true(1), fewer links will be allowed in each trunk group, i.e., a maximum of 4 links will be used in each trunk group, instead of the default limit of 8 links per trunk group.

sxswdisDesc.name: sxswdisDesc
sxswdisDesc.description: The description (0-32 bytes) of the software set currently being downloaded, or a description of the software set last downloaded since the last boot.

sxswdisAccess.name: sxswdisAccess
sxswdisAccess.description: The version of software that may be downloaded. Attempts to download other versions of software will be rejected. The value for swdisAccess is embedded within the software files that are to be distributed via TFTP. Its value may be derived from the names of the software files. the NMS operator may wish to use the following special values: protected (1) No software downloads will be accepted any-software (2) A software download of any version of new software will be accepted - this is the factory default

sxswdisWriteStatus.name: sxswdisWriteStatus
sxswdisWriteStatus.description: The status of the erase/write operation.

sxswdisConfigIp.name: sxswdisConfigIp
sxswdisConfigIp.description: The IP address of the NMS (i.e., any IP host) that is allowed to use TFTP to send/retrieve the configuration file of the device. A value of 0.0.0.0 (which is the factory specified default) prevents any NMS from obtaining access, while a value of 255.255.255.255 gives every NMS permission.

sxswdisConfigRetryTime.name: sxswdisConfigRetryTime
sxswdisConfigRetryTime.description: The number of seconds that the device will wait for an acknowledgment before it retransmits an unacknowledged TFTP data block. The factory specified default is 5 seconds.

sxswdisConfigTotalTimeout.name: sxswdisConfigTotalTimeout
sxswdisConfigTotalTimeout.description: The number of seconds that the device will wait for an acknowledgment to a data block before it cancels a TFTP session. The factory specified default is 25 seconds.

sxprotoTable.name: sxprotoTable
sxprotoTable.description: This table contains configuration information specify- ing the types of protocols used to bridge, route, translate, and filter frames for each port.

sxprotoEntry.name: sxprotoEntry
sxprotoEntry.description: Each entry in this table specifies which protocols are used by a particular port in the ES/1.

sxprotoIfIndex.name: sxprotoIfIndex
sxprotoIfIndex.description: Identifies the interface (port) to which this entry's information belongs. The value of this variable corresponds to ifIndex, as well as most of the other port identification values in related MIBs.

sxprotoBridge.name: sxprotoBridge
sxprotoBridge.description: Defines the bridging method to be applied to frames received at, or destined for, this port. Ethernet and FDDI ports may be configured for transparent, srt, or none. Token Ring ports may be configured for any of the four options. The UART may only be configured to none.

sxprotoSuppressBpdu.name: sxprotoSuppressBpdu
sxprotoSuppressBpdu.description: Allows transmission of spanning tree protocol packets to be suppressed. If normal(1), 802.1d spanning tree packets and source-routing spanning tree packets are transmitted as usual. If suppressed(2), these packets are not transmitted. This option may be needed for in- teroperability with non-802.1d spanning tree protocols (e.g., DEC LanBridge 100).

sxprotoRipListen.name: sxprotoRipListen
sxprotoRipListen.description: Specifies whether the port should listen for internet Routing Information Protocol (RFC-1058) packets, in order to build the routing table for the unit.

sxprotoTrunking.name: sxprotoTrunking
sxprotoTrunking.description: Specifies whether SMC's trunking protocol (an extension to the standard Spanning Tree) is to be used over this port.

sxsprotoCollisionRelief.name: sxsprotoCollisionRelief
sxsprotoCollisionRelief.description: Specifies whether the 10 Mbits Ethernet modified back-off algorithm is to be used. This option forces Ethernet port to stop the back-off timer when a transmit collision occured. It will start the timer again until no carrier on the wire. This option can reduce the number of transmit collisions. It may also slow down the transmit process under heavy loaded network.

sxtrunkTable.name: sxtrunkTable
sxtrunkTable.description: This table describes the trunking status and attributes of the interfaces that are configured for bridge trunking.

sxtrunkEntry.name: sxtrunkEntry
sxtrunkEntry.description: An entry exists in this table for each physical interface (port) that is configured for trunking.

sxtrunkIfIndex.name: sxtrunkIfIndex
sxtrunkIfIndex.description: Identifies a physical interface (port) which is configured for LAN trunking. The value of this variable corresponds to ifIndex, as well as most of the other port identification values in related MIBs.

sxtrunkState.name: sxtrunkState
sxtrunkState.description: If off(1) then this link has not been enabled for trunking. If closed(2) then this link has not yet received any Trunking PDUs. If oneway(3) then incoming Trunking PDUs do not indicate that our PDUs are being successfully received by the far end. If joined(4) then this link is actively participating in the trunk group. If perturbed(5) then this link is actively participating in the trunk group; however, the transmission of data packets has been temporarily stopped due to a change in membership of the group. If helddown(6) then an error has been detected and the link is being held out-of-service until the error clears. If broken(7) then this link has been configured for trunking, but the port is physically non-operational.

sxtrunkRemoteBridgeAddr.name: sxtrunkRemoteBridgeAddr
sxtrunkRemoteBridgeAddr.description: The MAC address portion of the bridge ID of the remote bridge.

sxtrunkRemoteIp.name: sxtrunkRemoteIp
sxtrunkRemoteIp.description: The IP address of the remote bridge, as reported by that bridge for administrative purposes.

sxtrunkLastError.name: sxtrunkLastError
sxtrunkLastError.description: The last reason for failure when the link is in closed, oneway, or helddown state.

sxtrunkLinkOrdinal.name: sxtrunkLinkOrdinal
sxtrunkLinkOrdinal.description: The position of this link within the trunk group.

sxtrunkLinkCount.name: sxtrunkLinkCount
sxtrunkLinkCount.description: The number of links within the trunk group.

sxtrunkLastChange.name: sxtrunkLastChange
sxtrunkLastChange.description: The number of seconds since sxtrunkState changed.

sxWorkGroupNextNumber.name: sxWorkGroupNextNumber
sxWorkGroupNextNumber.description: The next available workgroup number to be used. When creating a new workgroup, it is recommended to read the value of the variable and use it to key into the workgroup table.

sxWorkGroupCurrentCount.name: sxWorkGroupCurrentCount
sxWorkGroupCurrentCount.description: The total number of workgroups currently defined.

sxWorkGroupMaxCount.name: sxWorkGroupMaxCount
sxWorkGroupMaxCount.description: The maximum number of workgroups allowed.

sxWorkGroupTable.name: sxWorkGroupTable
sxWorkGroupTable.description: This table contains work group definitions for the interfaces.

sxWorkGroupEntry.name: sxWorkGroupEntry
sxWorkGroupEntry.description: Each entry in this table contains a definition of a work group.

sxWorkGroupNumber.name: sxWorkGroupNumber
sxWorkGroupNumber.description: An integer that identifies the work group, used as an index to this table.

sxWorkGroupPorts.name: sxWorkGroupPorts
sxWorkGroupPorts.description: A list of all ports within the group. The first octet specified ports 1-8, the second 9-16, etc.

sxWorkGroupType.name: sxWorkGroupType
sxWorkGroupType.description: The type of work group: all - no additional information needs to be supplied. ip - the IP network (and optionally, IP mask) must be supplied. ipx - the IPX network number may be supplied, or else all IPX network number will be assumed.

sxWorkGroupIpMask.name: sxWorkGroupIpMask
sxWorkGroupIpMask.description: The IP network mask, if set to 0, the default network mask is applied.

sxWorkGroupIpxNetwork.name: sxWorkGroupIpxNetwork
sxWorkGroupIpxNetwork.description: The IPX network number, 0 means all networks.

sxtrapControlTable.name: sxtrapControlTable
sxtrapControlTable.description: This table contains information about the severity of each trap and whether the trap is currently enable.

sxtrapEnabled.name: sxtrapEnabled
sxtrapEnabled.description: Enable or disable the generation of this trap.

sxtrapSeverity.name: sxtrapSeverity
sxtrapSeverity.description: A user-definable severity, indicating the importance of the trap.

sxtrapSeverityControlTable.name: sxtrapSeverityControlTable
sxtrapSeverityControlTable.description: This table contains information about whether a class of traps of a particular severity are enabled or disabled.

sxtrapSeverityControlSeverity.name: sxtrapSeverityControlSeverity
sxtrapSeverityControlSeverity.description: A user-definable severity, indicating the importance of the trap.

sxtrapSeverityEnable.name: sxtrapSeverityEnable
sxtrapSeverityEnable.description: Enable or disable all traps of a given severity level.

sxtrapIncludeText.name: sxtrapIncludeText
sxtrapIncludeText.description: Whether or not a formatted text string is included in the trap PDU.

sxtrapTime.name: sxtrapTime
sxtrapTime.description: The time, in centiseconds, which should expire between the sending of traps.

sxtrapRetry.name: sxtrapRetry
sxtrapRetry.description: The number of times any enterprise-specific trap is to be sent for a given event. PDUs are retried using a truncated exponential backoff: 2 seconds, 4 seoncs, 8 seconds, 16 seconds, and then 32 seconds for all succeeding intervals.

sxtrapEntryNumber.name: sxtrapEntryNumber
sxtrapEntryNumber.description: The number of traps that are in the sxtrapTable.

sxtrapTable.name: sxtrapTable
sxtrapTable.description: This table contains the latest traps that have been generated.

sxtrapEntryIndex.name: sxtrapEntryIndex
sxtrapEntryIndex.description: A number representing the order in which the trap occurred in time. This 32 bit number can wrap.

sxtrapEntryTimeStamp.name: sxtrapEntryTimeStamp
sxtrapEntryTimeStamp.description: The time at which the trap occurred.

sxtrapNumber.name: sxtrapNumber
sxtrapNumber.description: The specific trap number, as specified in the TRAP PDU.

sxtrapEntrySeverity.name: sxtrapEntrySeverity
sxtrapEntrySeverity.description: A user-definable severity, indicating the importance of the trap.

sxTempOKTrap.name: sxTempOKTrap
sxTempOKTrap.description: Sent whenever the module's temperature transitions from too hot to okay, and vice versa.

sxWriteStatusTrap.name: sxWriteStatusTrap
sxWriteStatusTrap.description: Sent when a bank of Flash EPROM has been erased. If sxswdisWriteStatus indicates success, then the unit is ready to be downloaded with the new software.

sxPortFunctionsTrap.name: sxPortFunctionsTrap
sxPortFunctionsTrap.description: Sent whenever the current functional state (active protocols) of the port has changed.

sxRxQueuesTrap.name: sxRxQueuesTrap
sxRxQueuesTrap.description: Sent whenever the number of times that the port's receiver has stopped receiving packets due to buffer space shortages has exceeded the port's limit.

sxTxStormFlagTrap.name: sxTxStormFlagTrap
sxTxStormFlagTrap.description: Sent whenever multicast storm protection has been invoked for the port.

sxTxCongestsTrap.name: sxTxCongestsTrap
sxTxCongestsTrap.description: Sent whenever packets destined for the unit itself were discarded due to lack of buffer space.

sxFilterThreshTrap.name: sxFilterThreshTrap
sxFilterThreshTrap.description: Sent whenever usage of a port's combination filter has exceeded the filter's limits.

sxDebugStringIdTrap.name: sxDebugStringIdTrap
sxDebugStringIdTrap.description: Send whenever the unit has a debug text string to be displayed. The text strings are sent in a stream-like fashion.

sxLpbkOperationTrap.name: sxLpbkOperationTrap
sxLpbkOperationTrap.description: Send whenever the unit has finished a loop back test, or a loop back error has been detected.

sxTrunkStateTrap.name: sxTrunkStateTrap
sxTrunkStateTrap.description: A trunking state change transition has occurred. The possible transitions are: CLOSED-ONEWAY ONEWAY-PERTURBED PERTURBED-JOINED JOINED-HELDDOWN CLOSED-HELDDOWN ONEWAY-HELDDOWN PERTURBED-HELDDOWN

sxTrunkBridgeAddrTrap.name: sxTrunkBridgeAddrTrap
sxTrunkBridgeAddrTrap.description: The associated trunking MAC address of the bridge ID of the remote bridge has changed.

sxTrunkIPAddrTrap.name: sxTrunkIPAddrTrap
sxTrunkIPAddrTrap.description: The associated trunking IP address of the remote bridge has changed.

sxTrunkErrorTrap.name: sxTrunkErrorTrap
sxTrunkErrorTrap.description: An error has occurred in trunking.

sxTrunkLinkOrdinalTrap.name: sxTrunkLinkOrdinalTrap
sxTrunkLinkOrdinalTrap.description: The port's index in the trunking group has changed.

sxTrunkLinkCountTrap.name: sxTrunkLinkCountTrap
sxTrunkLinkCountTrap.description: The number of ports in the trunking group has changed.

sxDiagUnitBootedTrap.name: sxDiagUnitBootedTrap
sxDiagUnitBootedTrap.description: The unit has booted. sxadminFatalErr contains information about why the unit rebooted.

sxStorageFailureTrap.name: sxStorageFailureTrap
sxStorageFailureTrap.description: Sent if the unit's Configuration EEPROM has failed. The unit will not be able to reboot, and must be returned to the factory.

sxPortCongestedTrap.name: sxPortCongestedTrap
sxPortCongestedTrap.description: Sent whenever outbound congestion control has been invoked for the port.

sxTopChangeBegunTrap.name: sxTopChangeBegunTrap
sxTopChangeBegunTrap.description: The spanning tree topology has begun to change.

sxTopChangeEndTrap.name: sxTopChangeEndTrap
sxTopChangeEndTrap.description: The spanning tree topology has stopped changing.

sxIfErrorsTrap.name: sxIfErrorsTrap
sxIfErrorsTrap.description: Sent whenever the number of hardware errors in received and transmitted packets has exceeded the port's limit.

sxStRootIDTrap.name: sxStRootIDTrap
sxStRootIDTrap.description: The spanning tree root bridge ID for the unit has changed.

sxStRootCostTrap.name: sxStRootCostTrap
sxStRootCostTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree cost to the root bridge has changed.

sxStRootPortTrap.name: sxStRootPortTrap
sxStRootPortTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree root port has changed.

sxStMaxAgeTrap.name: sxStMaxAgeTrap
sxStMaxAgeTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree maximum age has changed.

sxStHelloTimeTrap.name: sxStHelloTimeTrap
sxStHelloTimeTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree hello time has changed.

sxStForwardDelayTrap.name: sxStForwardDelayTrap
sxStForwardDelayTrap.description: The unit's spanning tree forward delay time has changed.

sxStDesigRootTrap.name: sxStDesigRootTrap
sxStDesigRootTrap.description: The Root Bridge ID in received Spanning Tree Configuration BPDUs from the port has changed.

sxStPortDesigBridgeTrap.name: sxStPortDesigBridgeTrap
sxStPortDesigBridgeTrap.description: The bridge ID of the spanning tree designated bridge of the LAN/WAN to which the port is attached has changed.

sxStPortDesigCostTrap.name: sxStPortDesigCostTrap
sxStPortDesigCostTrap.description: The cost to the spanning tree root bridge from the designated port of the LAN/WAN to which the port is attached has changed.

sxStPortDesigPortTrap.name: sxStPortDesigPortTrap
sxStPortDesigPortTrap.description: The port ID of the spanning tree designated port of the LAN/WAN to which the port is attached has changed.

sxStPortStateTrap.name: sxStPortStateTrap
sxStPortStateTrap.description: The spanning tree state of the port has changed.

sxhwDiagTrap.name: sxhwDiagTrap
sxhwDiagTrap.description: Sent whenever the unit's diagnostics have indicated an error.
